that the 1940, after 17 years of nationalist government, Chile adopted one of the most progressive constitutions in the world. The main theme of the constitution summarizing the triple concept of rights: freedom, equality and fraternity. The rights of women were recognized, differentiated by the law on labor safety. The legal preamble has included recognition that Chile has to secure the progressive political and social development. The Founding Father Augustina recited the famous lines: “In Chile we struggle for the throne and we walk in the Name of the Constitution”.

In the years after the adoption of the Constitution with the main strength in the economy ran by the American investment construction of the Pinochet regime. The powerful new international role and influence relied on the exploitation latent hostile relations with neighboring countries, especially Bolivia.

Modest economic progress in decades agofrom 1990 to 2000was made under the conditions of transformations in local business political structure, partially undoing the real but not visible results obtained until the mid-nineties. The economic growth development of the economy in the late 20 years of the last century deserves due attention. However, entire corruptions and inappropriate management of privatization processes have deprived most of this progress of national teeth. Taxes have been converted inconvenient for the rich, and reform of labor regulations made the number of strikes increase dramatically.
